<span id="freeTextContainer18118198792071247890">Excellent idea of a story but, executed in an ordinary fashion. The plot was probably lost in translation.<br/><br/>Asha to me was the real prisoner of life having endured abuse and miserable lifestyle, she found in a real life prisoner some freedom and strength. She found the spice &amp; the purpose her life always lacked. Rashid on the other hand is the prisoner who enjoyed more freedom &quot;visitors &amp; married life&quot; between the bars of the prison. <br/><br/>One of the best parts of the book was the graphic details of the</span>
  <span id="freeText18118198792071247890" style="display:none">Excellent idea of a story but, executed in an ordinary fashion. The plot was probably lost in translation.<br /><br />Asha to me was the real prisoner of life having endured abuse and miserable lifestyle, she found in a real life prisoner some freedom and strength. She found the spice &amp; the purpose her life always lacked. Rashid on the other hand is the prisoner who enjoyed more freedom "visitors &amp; married life" between the bars of the prison. <br /><br />One of the best parts of the book was the graphic details of the abortion experience. <br /><br />This was not a love story in my books despite the writer's persistence.</span>
